I, Xandor Voxbane, was in Highpass mid afternoon and decided it would be good to go to Kael and bind there in case I was needed for anything such as guided sight seeing tours through the city. I ran to what I like to call the &quot;Nexus&quot; in North Karana and caught the &quot;teleport&quot; to the &quot;moon&quot;. From there I was &quot;teleported&quot; back down to Great Divide, where I made the run to Eastern Wastes, and then to Kael. I arrived in the city of the giants and was readied my &quot;bind&quot; spell, like I had done a thousand times before. I did a quick perimeter scan, checking for anything that might try to eat me. When I was satisfied that the coast was clear, I broke invis to bind myself. Little did I know, that this time it wasn't a normal bind spell I was casting, but rather an evil gate spell that would send me all the way back to the Ruins of Old Sebilis. The next thing I know I'm thinking to myself &quot;Hmmm that's odd...I don't remember there being a zoning component to bind...Oh CRAP! I'm in Old Sebilis&quot;. So then I make my escape to Emerald Jungle where a very nice friend, Cetheile picks me up and takes me to Wakening lands. From there I ran through the city, bound myself and logged. End of Story...or is it....<br>
<br>
I, Kantle X'Dor, get a port in to Wakening Lands a little bit later and ready my &quot;bind&quot; spell thinking it would &quot;idea&quot; in case I needed to gate back to the entrance for any reason. I cast it and without checking to see if it was a success or not put the spell away, and camp out for dinner. A short while later, the raid gets under way, and we begin moving up through the city. We get to just outside the arena, and I learn that there is a rogue at the entrance that needs to be Call of the Hero'd to the fun, so I group up with Mysticleve, our resident CoH mage and ready gate to go back and get the rogue. The next thing I know I see &quot;Loading Please Wait&quot; and I think to myself &quot;Hmmm...I don't rember needed to load if I do a gate to a spot within the same zone&quot;. The next thing I know I am looking at the forge in Highpass where I had been smithing earlier in the day. Luckily for me I'm a friendly dark elf and am on good terms with the halflings, so I run out to Misty Thicket and get a port back to the action from Somberlain. All the while, everyone else was getting wiped out by the Idol of Rallos Zek, so you never even knew...muahahahaha<br>
